., <em>An Introduction to Chaotic Dynamical Systems</em></p><p>3. Grandy, R. E. and Warner, R., <em>Philosophical Grounds of Rationality</em></p><p>4. Russell, C. A., <em>Science and Social Change, 1700\u20131900</em></p><p>5. Keynes, J. M., <em>A Tract on Monetary Reform</em></p><p>6. Le Guin, U. K., <em>The Dispossessed</em></p><p>7. Lenin, V. I., <em>Selected Works, Volume 3</em></p><p>8. Locke, J., <em>An Essay Concerning Human Understanding</em></p><p>9. Wells, H. G., <em>The War of the Worlds</em></p><p>10. Mountevans, Admiral Lord, <em>The Desolate Antarctic</em></p><p>11. Rousseau, J.-J., <em>The Discourses and Other Early Political Writings</em></p><p>12. Tolansky, S., <em>Introduction to Atomic Physics</em></p><div><hr></div><p><em>Thanks George for showing us around. </em></p>",
